'''Yashuvhi''' was the native language of the [[Yashuvhi]] people, Human settlers from [[Yashuvhu/Legends|Yashuvhu]].

Yashuvhi was a derivative of [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Basic]] language, although using inflections instead of prepositions. This could be because Yashuvhu was a Human settling which had lost contact with the galaxy, or because, millennia ago, an unidentified [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] crashed on Yashuvhu and became an important member of the community (The word "Jedi" was used with an almost religious fervor).

First-contact specialists on ''[[Pathfinder III]]'' could easily learn the basics of Yashuvhi when they re-discovered the world on [[33 BBY/Legends|33 BBY]].

